title: Measurement and analysis of excitation functions of the residues from 12C + 89Y: A major production route for 97Ru

x4freetext: Measurement and analysis of excitation functions of
the residues from 12C + 89Y: A major production route
for 97Ru

x4codes.hlp: Indian Institute of Technology, Ropar, India
Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics, Kolkata, India

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.99, p.064609 (2019)

x4codes.hlp: Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai, India

x4freetext: BARC-TIFR pelletron accelerator
The natural 89Y foils having thickness of 1.8-2.0
mg/cm2 and the Al foils of thickness 1.5 mg/cm2 were
prepared by proper rolling.
The foils were mounted on the Al-rings of 12 mm inner
and 22 mm outer diameter.
A high purity germanium detector attached with
a PC operating with the GENIE-2K software.
The efficiency calibration of the detector was done by
using a standard gamma-ray source, 152Eu.
The energy resolution of the detector was 2.0 keV at
the 1332 keV photo-peak of 60Co.
The total charge during irradiation was
collected on a Faraday cup and duration of irradiation
was varied from 1-3 hours.
A total of five such Y-Al foil stacks were
irradiated with a slight overlap in energy.
The total error in the cross section
measurement are
foil thickness              (~2-3%)
efficiency calibration of the detector
projectile beam current     (~6-7%)
counting statistics         (~6-7%)
